update post cache "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
=================================================================

NAME
----

update post cache - Updates the cache for each post passed in.

SYNOPSIS
--------

Updates the cache for each post passed in.

**NOTE**: despite name, it does not take a single post object or ID; it
takes **only** an array of post objects.

-   @usedby
    [Function\_Reference/update\_page\_cache](/index.php?title=Function_Reference/update_page_cache&action=edit&redlink=1 "Function Reference/update page cache (page does not exist)")
    Aliased by this function.

-   @package WordPress
-   @subpackage Cache

SINCE
-----

1.5.1

PARAMS
------

array \$posts Array of post objects

SOURCE
------

`update_post_cache()` is located in `wp-includes/post.php`.

